cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.SI 

This paper deals with the reconstruction of hyperspectral images using a low dimensional manifold model. The most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the paper deals with image reconstruction. The second likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper uses a point integral method to solve a Laplace-Beltrami equation, which is a common technique in machine learning. The third likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory) as the paper deals with missing data and the reconstruction of images. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as the paper uses numerical simulations to validate the proposed method. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper deals with the analysis of a low dimensional patch manifold in hyperspectral images.
